(FieldBean)abstract.description: If true the generated model will be initially set as abstract class.

(FieldBean)author.description: The autor of something e,g. a class.

(FieldBean)classPath.description: Defines the classpath target path when generating java classes and resources beneath module like 'src/main/java' or 'src/test/resources'.

(FieldBean)create.description: If true will create a Java class.

(FieldBean)creationDate.description: Used to define the creation of an item.

(FieldBean)dbAnnotated.description: If true a db annotation will be generated for java instance vars.

(FieldBean)description.description: A description of the model used by every model extending BaseClassImpl.

(FieldBean)fieldKeys.description: A list of field keys for the model configuration.

(FieldBean)interfaces.description: A comma separeted list of interface keys.

(FieldBean)localFieldKeys.description: A list of field as proivided by the model configuration.

(FieldBean)modelKey.description: The model name for the bean/action object @ModelConfig.

(FieldBean)modelKeyPluralLower.description: The plural lower version of modelKey.

(FieldBean)module.description: Defines a target module where generating occurs.

(FieldBean)moduleScope.description: Defines scope of the configuration within module, eg 'test' or 'main' .

(FieldBean)scope.description: A scope for the cache value.

(FieldBean)superKey.description: A key for the super class of a class.
